    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-02-11T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-02-11T20:00:00-05:00" n="505"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d505">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">862.6362/2–1146: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        United States Political Adviser for Germany</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Murphy</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-02-11T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 11, 1946—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>387. French Govt has presented to Dept <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi>
                    <note n="57" xml:id="d505fn57">Dated February 8, not printed.</note> protesting
                    statement allegedly made by US representative Economic Directorate in meeting of
                    Jan 10. US position described as having been that since German domestic coal
                    requirements were not being met that no expansion in coal exports could be
                    considered. French position described as having been that coal exports should be
                    maximized within limits of transport capabilities. French protest made on basis
                    alleged US position violates July coal directive.<note n="58" xml:id="d505fn58"
                        >For text of the directive issued to General Eisenhower by the Joint Chiefs
                        of Staff, July 26, 1945, see <ref target="frus1945Berlinv02#pg_1028">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, The Conference of Berlin (The
                            Potsdam Conference), 1945, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p.
                            1028</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Would you report fully relevant portion Jan 10 meeting.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
